Hi Mohsin, you didn't do anything wrong. I had the same problem. It 
seems that the new version of the Matlab toolbox doesn't have the 
"display.m" file which lets it show the properties (as you expected). 
The gas object has been created, but it's not displaying the properties.

Try putting the following text into a file named "display.m" within the 
"@Solution" directory and see what happens:
-----
function display(a)

s = [sprintf('\n       temperature         %12.6g  K\n', temperature(a)) 
  ...
      sprintf('       pressure            %12.6g  Pa\n', pressure(a)) ...
      sprintf('       density             %12.6g  kg/m^3\n', density(a)) ...
      sprintf('       mean mol. weight    %12.6g  amu', ...
	     meanMolecularWeight(a))];
disp(s);

nsp = nSpecies(a);
x = moleFractions(a);
y = massFractions(a);

s = [...
     sprintf('\n                           X                 Y   \n') ...
     sprintf('                     -------------     ------------ ')];
     disp(s);

     for k = 1:nsp
       disp(sprintf('%18s   %12.6e     %12.6e', char(speciesName(a,k)), 
x(k), y(k)));
     end
disp(' ');
------

Hope that works out,
Michael
